(94, 1, 10, 'entries', 'Elena', NULL, '{\"Tabla\":\"entries\",\"Data\":{\"permalink\":\"-decorative-dilems:-large-tiles-vs-small\",\"author\":\"Elena\",\"title\":\" DECORATIVE DILEMS: LARGE TILES VS SMALL\",\"abstract\":\"\\u003Cpre id=\\u0022tw-target-text\\u0022 class=\\u0022tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small\\u0022 dir=\\u0022ltr\\u0022 data-placeholder=\\u0022Traducci\\u0026oacute;n\\u0022 data-fulltext=\\u0022\\u0022\\u003E\\u003Cspan lang=\\u0022en\\u0022 tabindex=\\u00220\\u0022\\u003EAre you going to reform your bathroom? Your kitchen? Do you want to change the tiles and do not know what would be better? Big without joints? Small subway type? Here are some keys that will help you decide\\u003C\\/span\\u003E\\u003C\\/pre\\u003E\",\"content\":\"\\u003Ch5 id=\\u0022tw-target-text\\u0022 class=\\u0022tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small\\u0022 dir=\\u0022ltr\\u0022 data-placeholder=\\u0022Traducci\\u0026oacute;n\\u0022\\u003E\\u003Cstrong\\u003E\\u003Cspan lang=\\u0022en\\u0022 tabindex=\\u00220\\u0022\\u003ESMALL TILES FOR OPEN KITCHENS\\u003C\\/span\\u003E\\u003C\\/strong\\u003E\\u003C\\/h5\\u003E\\r\\n\\u003Ch5 class=\\u0022tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small\\u0022 dir=\\u0022ltr\\u0022 data-placeholder=\\u0022Traducci\\u0026oacute;n\\u0022\\u003E\\u003Cspan lang=\\u0022en\\u0022 tabindex=\\u00220\\u0022\\u003EIn a kitchen open to the dining room, small tiles are a good option. You can place them only on the parapet and paint the rest of the space so that the different rooms are better integrated. If you choose the tiles of the same color as the painting, the effect will be much more harmonious. \\u003C\\/span\\u003E\\u003C\\/h5\\u003E\\r\\n\\u003Ch5 class=\\u0022tw-data-text tw-ta tw-text-small\\u0022 dir=\\u0022ltr\\u0022 data-placeholder=\\u0022Traducci\\u0026oacute;n\\u0022\\u003E\\u003Cstrong\\u003E\\u003Cspan lang=\\u0022en\\u0022 tabindex=\\u00220\\u0022\\u003ELARGE TILES EXTEND \\u003C\\/span\\u003E\\u003C\\/strong\\u003E\\u003C\\/h5\\u003E\\r\\n\\u003Ch5 cla